title: Legal Marijuana Faces Another Federal Hurdle: Taxes
description: Shops say they are being forced to pay crippling federal taxes because of a law aimed at preventing drug dealers from claiming smuggling costs and couriers as write-offs.

title: Quarterback Winston Files Counterclaim Against Rape Accuser
description: Heisman-winning quarterback Jameis Winston on Friday filed a counterclaim against a woman who accused him of raping her in 2012 while she was a student at Florida State University, court records show.

title: Uber Fund-Raising Points to $50 Billion Valuation
description: The new capital will not be used primarily for expansion purposes, unlike Uber’s previous financing rounds — instead, the funding is strategic, with an eye on partnerships.

title: North Korea Says It Test-Fired Missile From Submarine
description: North Korea’s test, if confirmed, would pose a new challenge to the United States and its regional allies, South Korea and Japan.

title: One Constant for Adam Skelos in a Life of Stumbles: His Powerful Father
description: Since his arrest, the portrait of Mr. Skelos, 32, that has emerged is one of a young man whose life seemed to lose traction during late adolescence and who struggled professionally.

title: Frustrated Jury in Etan Patz Trial, but No Rancor for the Holdout
description: In a rare post-trial news conference, several jurors explained the course of their deliberations. None hinted at any negative feelings toward the one juror who could not be persuaded to convict.

title: Jurors in Etan Patz Case Fall One Vote Shy of a Conviction
description: A judge declared a mistrial in the Etan Patz case on Friday, and jurors later said a lone holdout would not vote to convict Pedro Hernandez.

title: Illinois Supreme Court Rejects Lawmakers’ Pension Overhaul
description: The court found that the proposed fixes lawmakers had agreed to over a year ago diminished the pension and violated the Illinois Constitution.

title: A Wartime Anniversary for Planes and Memories
description: Aging veterans were among those watching as dozens of fighter planes and bombers from World War II buzzed over Washington on the 70th anniversary of the Allied victory in Europe.

title: Politics Are Set Aside as Thousands Mourn Officer Brian Moore
description: Nearly a week after he was shot and killed while on patrol in Queens, Officer Moore was laid to rest on Friday surrounded by a sea of blue.

title: Crime Scene: The Police Car Provides a Home on the Job, and a False Sense of Safety
description: To an officer, the car is, psychologically, a safe place. But in reality, it may make them more vulnerable.

title: White House Moves to Fix 2 Key Consumer Complaints About Health Care Law
description: Health officials will require insurers to update doctor directories and hope to help patients estimate out-of-pocket costs.

title: Court Ruling on N.S.A.’s Data Collection Jolts Both Defenders and Reformers
description: A United States Court of Appeals decision that the agency’s bulk collection of phone records is illegal has complicated bipartisan efforts to make substantial changes to the program.

title: Nepalese Village, Devastated by Quake, Is Left to Cope as International Attention Shifts
description: As relief teams struggle to reach earthquake victims in isolated areas, some aid workers said they were worried that attention had already strayed from Nepal.

title: Etan Patz’s Disappearance Has a Lasting Impact on Parenting
description: When Etan, 6, vanished from a Manhattan sidewalk in 1979, it changed the way parents raised their children, and the kind of parents those children became.

title: ESPN Is Splitting With Bill Simmons, Who Offers an Uncharacteristic Word Count: Zero
description: John Skipper, ESPN’s president, said the company would not renew its contract with Simmons, an outspoken personality who said nothing publicly on Friday about the move.

title: Frida Kahlo Is Having a Moment
description: Her face is on T-shirts and magnets, but that has not diminished the public’s fascination.

title: Airport Security Advances Clash With Privacy Issues
description: New technologies that could ease scanning or locate wayward passengers are bumping into privacy protections and efforts to cut federal spending.

title: Retiring: New Math for Retirees and the 4% Withdrawal Rule
description: Though the concept has been celebrated and criticized, it has come under scrutiny again, particularly as people are now retiring during a period of low interest rates.

title: ArtsBeat: Millepied to Take On ‘Vertigo’ at Cannes
description: Benjamin Millepied, the director of the Paris Opera Ballet, will present a piece at Cannes set to music from “Vertigo.”
